<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>CFBundleIconFile</key>
	<string>com.apple.mail</string>
	<key>CFBundleIdentifier</key>
	<string>ptujec.LaunchBar.action.PasteMailURLScheme</string>
	<key>CFBundleName</key>
	<string>Paste Mail URL Scheme</string>
	<key>CFBundleVersion</key>
	<string>4.0.2</string>
	<key>LBDescription</key>
	<dict>
		<key>LBAuthor</key>
		<string>Christian Bender</string>
		<key>LBEmail</key>
		<string></string>
		<key>LBSummary</key>
		<string>⏎ = Paste URL only, ⇧⏎ = MD, ⌘⏎ = RTF 

This action might be a little overkill in terms of options, but its basic function is very simple. Just run the action to paste the URL of an open or selected email into the current text field.

Hold ⇧ for Markdown or ⌘ for Rich Text Format. By default, this will use the email subject as the title. If you hit space before running the action, you can even enter a custom title.</string>
		<key>LBTwitter</key>
		<string>@Ptujec</string>
		<key>LBUpdateURL</key>
		<string>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Ptujec/LaunchBar/master/URL-Scheme-Actions/Paste%20Mail%20URL%20Scheme.lbaction/Contents/Info.plist</string>
		<key>LBWebsiteURL</key>
		<string>https://github.com/Ptujec/LaunchBar/tree/master/URL-Scheme-Actions#mail</string>
	</dict>
	<key>LBRequiredApplication</key>
	<string>com.apple.mail</string>
	<key>LBScripts</key>
	<dict>
		<key>LBDefaultScript</key>
		<dict>
			<key>LBAcceptedArgumentTypes</key>
			<array>
				<string>string</string>
			</array>
			<key>LBKeepWindowActive</key>
			<true/>
			<key>LBResultType</key>
			<string>unknown</string>
			<key>LBReturnsResult</key>
			<true/>
			<key>LBScriptName</key>
			<string>default.js</string>
		</dict>
	</dict>
	<key>LBTextInputTitle</key>
	<string>Title for Markdown or RTF link</string>
</dict>
</plist>
